-- в”Ђв”Ђ Hive в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Flexible project management platform with Gantt, Kanban and Table views, native chat, time tracking and an AI assistant.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Freemium$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free; paid plans from $5/user/month$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2015, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$51-200 employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$New York City, New York, United States$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Hive Review 2026: Features, Pricing and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Hive review 2026: explore this New York project management platform's views, AI assistant, pricing tiers and how it compares to Asana and ClickUp.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Hive is a flexible project management and productivity platform headquartered in New York City, founded in 2015 by John Furneaux, who serves as CEO, along with co-founders Eric Typaldos (CTO) and Eric Maciel. The company has raised approximately $28 million in funding from investors including Comcast Ventures, Tribeca Venture Partners and Rembrandt Partners, with a notable $10.6 million Series A round in 2021 led by Comcast Ventures. Hive is based at 33 W 17th Street in Manhattan and employs a team generally estimated in the range of 100 to 200 people. The platform has been used by well-known brands including WeWork, Netflix and Uber, and is positioned as an all-in-one work management tool that consolidates project planning, team collaboration and productivity tracking into a single workspace, competing directly against Asana, Monday.com, ClickUp, Trello and Wrike. Architecturally, Hive is a cloud-based, browser-accessible web application (with desktop and mobile companion apps) built around flexible project views: users can switch between Gantt chart, Kanban board, calendar, table (spreadsheet-style) and portfolio views for the same underlying project data, letting different team members work in the view that suits them without duplicating data entry. Beyond views, Hive bundles native team chat and direct messaging so conversations happen alongside tasks rather than in a separate app, built-in email integration that lets users send and receive email from within Hive, time tracking for logging hours against tasks and projects, shareable web forms for intake requests that automatically convert into tasks, resource and workload management, proofing and approval workflows for creative and content review, and an AI assistant that can help summarize project status, draft updates, and automate routine work. Hive also integrates with widely used tools including Slack, Zoom, and cloud storage providers like Google Drive, and offers an Enterprise API for custom integrations. Hive's pricing follows a freemium structure with four tiers. The Free plan costs $0 forever and supports up to 10 workspace members with 200MB of storage, unlimited tasks, collaborative notes, native chat and email integration, suited to individuals or very small teams doing lightweight project management. The Starter plan is priced at $5 per user per month and adds unlimited storage, up to 10 projects, Gantt chart views, cloud storage integrations, an in-app calendar, Zoom and Slack integrations, and access to the AI Assistant. The Teams plan, priced at $12 per user per month, removes the workspace member cap, adds custom fields, labels and statuses, shareable intake forms, time tracking, portfolios and team-wide sharing. The Enterprise plan uses custom pricing and adds enhanced security controls, unlimited onboarding support, a dedicated Customer Success Manager, an Enterprise API, and access to Hive's Professional Services team for implementation support. Annual billing saves customers roughly 33% compared to monthly billing, and Hive offers a 14-day free trial with full feature access and no credit card required, plus discounted pricing for qualifying non-profit organizations. Hive's target audience spans small teams needing simple task tracking up through marketing agencies, creative teams and larger cross-functional organizations that need flexible views, built-in collaboration and workload visibility without stitching together separate chat, project management and time-tracking tools. It differentiates from Asana and Monday.com primarily through its native chat and email integration living inside the same workspace as tasks, and from ClickUp through a comparatively simpler, less configuration-heavy interface aimed at faster onboarding.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'e05880b5-22df-4a10-a038-632711020632';

